# SoK Paper LaTeX Compile Guide

All compile commands run from **`paper/draft/`**. Do not compile from the repo root.

## Standard build (four passes)

```bash
cd paper/draft

pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode main.tex   # pass 1 — [?] citations are normal
bibtex main                                   # references.bib → main.bbl
pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode main.tex   # pass 2 — insert bibliography
pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode main.tex   # pass 3 — fix cross-refs
```

Shortcut: `make paper` (same four steps).

## Layout (do not duplicate)

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `draft/main.tex` | Single source document |
| `draft/references.bib` | BibTeX database (working copy) |
| `draft/IEEEtran.cls`, `draft/IEEEtran.bst` | IEEE template + BibTeX style |
| `draft/figures/fig*.pdf` | Generated figure PDFs |
| `draft/figures/scripts/` | Matplotlib scripts (`generate_all.sh`) |
| `bibliography/references.bib` | Canonical bib (sync into draft when edited) |

- Figures use `\graphicspath{{figures/}}` and `\includegraphics[width=\columnwidth]{...}` (or `\textwidth` in `figure*`).
- Bibliography uses `\bibliographystyle{IEEEtran}` and `\bibliography{references}` — not a manual `\begin{thebibliography}` block.
- Never edit `main.bbl` by hand; change `references.bib` and re-run the four-pass sequence.

## Before compiling

1. **Figures changed or missing?** `make figures` (runs `figures/scripts/generate_all.sh`).
2. **Edited canonical bib?** `make sync-bib` copies `../bibliography/references.bib` into draft.
3. **New `\cite{key}` in body?** Add the entry to `bibliography/references.bib`, sync, then compile. Uncited bib entries are omitted from the PDF.

## Optional cleanup

`make clean` removes aux/log/bbl and figure PDFs only (keeps scripts and `.sty`).

## Common failures

- **Missing `.sty`**: `threeparttable.sty` is vendored in `draft/`.
- **Missing fonts** (e.g. `pcrr7t`): use a full TeX Live / MacTeX install, not `texlive-basic` alone.
- **Undefined citations after full build**: key missing from `references.bib` or not cited in `main.tex` body text.
